<?php
return ['domain'=>NULL,'plural-forms'=>'nplurals=1; plural=0;','messages'=>['<strong>Pending Users</strong>: Pending users are users who have successfully logged in to the site, but who haven\'t yet been approved (or blocked) by you.'=>'<strong>待定用户</strong>: 待定用户是指已成功 登录站点，但尚未获得您的批准(或阻止)的用户。','<strong>Approved Users</strong>: Approved users have access to the site once they successfully log in.'=>'<strong>审核用户</strong>: 获得批准的用户在成功登录后即可访问该站点。','<strong>Blocked Users</strong>: Blocked users will receive an error message when they try to visit the site after authenticating.'=>'<strong>禁止用户</strong>: 被禁止的用户在通过身份验证后尝试访问站点时将收到一条错误消息。','Users in the <strong>Pending</strong> list appear automatically after a new user tries to log in from the configured external authentication service. You can add users to the <strong>Approved</strong> or <strong>Blocked</strong> lists by typing them in manually, or by clicking the <em>Approve</em> or <em>Block</em> buttons next to a user in the <strong>Pending</strong> list.'=>'新用户尝试从配置的外部身份验证服务登录后，"<strong>待定</strong>"列表中的用户会自动出现。您可以手动输入用户，或单击 "<strong>待定</strong>"列表中用户旁边的 "<strong>批准</strong>"或 "<strong>阻止</strong>"按钮，将其添加到 "已<em>批准</em>"或 "已<em>阻止</em>"列表中。','Access Lists'=>'访问列表','<strong>Who can log in to the site?</strong>: Choose the level of access restriction you\'d like to use on your site here. You can leave the site open to anyone with a WordPress account or an account on an external service like Google, CAS, or LDAP, or restrict it to WordPress users and only the external users that you specify via the <em>Access Lists</em>.'=>'<strong>谁可以登录网站？</strong>在这里选择您想在网站上使用的访问限制级别。您可以让拥有 WordPress 账户或 Google、CAS 或 LDAP 等外部服务账户的任何人都可以登录网站，也可以限制只有 WordPress 用户和您通过<em>访问列表</em>指定的外部用户可以登录网站。','<strong>Which role should receive email notifications about pending users?</strong>: If you\'ve restricted access to <strong>approved users</strong>, you can determine which WordPress users will receive a notification email everytime a new external user successfully logs in and is added to the pending list. All users of the specified role will receive an email, and the external user will get a message (specified below) telling them their access is pending approval.'=>'<strong>哪个角色应收到有关待处理用户的电子邮件通知？</strong>如果您限制了<strong>已批准用户</strong>的访问权限，您可以确定每次有新的外部用户成功登录并被添加到待定列表时，哪些 WordPress 用户会收到通知邮件。指定角色的所有用户都会收到一封电子邮件，而外部用户则会收到一条信息（如下所示），告诉他们他们的访问正在等待批准。','<strong>What message should pending users see after attempting to log in?</strong>: Here you can specify the exact message a new external user will see once they try to log in to the site for the first time.'=>'<strong>待处理用户在尝试登录后会看到什么信息？</strong> 在这里，您可以指定新的外部用户在首次尝试登录网站时会看到的确切信息。','Login Access'=>'登录访问','<strong>Who can view the site?</strong>: You can restrict the site\'s visibility by only allowing logged in users to see pages. If you do so, you can customize the specifics about the site\'s privacy using the settings below.'=>'<strong>谁可以查看网站？</strong>您可以限制网站的可见性，只允许登录用户查看页面。如果这样做，您可以使用下面的设置自定义网站隐私的具体内容。','<strong>What pages (if any) should be available to everyone?</strong>: If you\'d like to declare certain pages on your site as always public (such as the course syllabus, introduction, or calendar), specify those pages here. These pages will always be available no matter what access restrictions exist.'=>'<strong>哪些页面（如果有的话）应该对所有人开放？</strong> 如果您想将网站上的某些页面（如课程大纲、简介或日历）永久公开，请在此处指定这些页面。无论存在何种访问限制，这些页面都将始终可用。','<strong>What happens to people without access when they visit a <em>private</em> page?</strong>: Choose the response anonymous users receive when visiting the site. You can choose between immediately taking them to the <strong>login screen</strong>, or simply showing them a <strong>message</strong>.'=>'<strong>访问私人页面时，没有访问权限<em>的人会发生什么情况</em>页面？</strong>：选择匿名用户在访问时收到的响应网站。您可以选择立即将他们带到<strong>登录屏幕</strong>，或者只是向他们显示<strong>一条消息</strong>。','<strong>What happens to people without access when they visit a <em>public</em> page?</strong>: Choose the response anonymous users receive when visiting a page on the site marked as public. You can choose between showing them the page without any message, or showing them a the page with a message above the content.'=>'<strong>访问公共场所时，没有访问权限<em>的人会发生什么情况</em>页面？</strong>：选择匿名用户在访问时收到的响应网站上标记为公共的页面。您可以选择向他们展示没有任何消息的页面，或向他们显示带有消息的页面内容。','<strong>What message should people without access see?</strong>: If you chose to show new users a <strong>message</strong> above, type that message here.'=>'<strong>没有访问权限的人应该看到什么消息？</strong>：如果你选择要向新用户显示上面<strong>的消息</strong>，请在此处键入该消息。','Public Access'=>'公共访问','<strong>Type of external service to authenticate against</strong>: Choose which authentication service type you will be using. You\'ll have to fill out different fields below depending on which service you choose.'=>'<strong>要进行身份验证的外部服务类型</strong>：选择您将使用的身份验证服务类型。你必须填写下面的不同字段取决于您选择的服务。','<strong>Enable OAuth2 Logins</strong>: Choose if you want to allow users to log in with one of the supported OAuth2 providers. You will need to enter your API Client ID and Secret to enable these logins.'=>'<strong>启用 OAuth2 登录</strong>：选择是否允许用户使用受支持的 OAuth2 提供程序之一登录。您需要输入用于启用这些登录的 API 客户端 ID 和密钥。','<strong>Enable Google Logins</strong>: Choose if you want to allow users to log in with their Google Account credentials. You will need to enter your API Client ID and Secret to enable Google Logins.'=>'<strong>启用 Google 登录</strong>：选择是否允许用户使用他们的 Google 帐户凭据登录。您将需要输入您的 API 用于启用 Google 登录的客户端 ID 和密码。','<strong>Enable CAS Logins</strong>: Choose if you want to allow users to log in with via CAS (Central Authentication Service). You will need to enter details about your CAS server (host, port, and path) to enable CAS Logins.'=>'<strong>启用 CAS 登录</strong>：选择是否允许用户登录通过CAS（中央身份验证服务）。您需要输入有关您的 CAS 服务器（主机、端口和路径）的详细信息，以启用 CAS 登录。','<strong>Enable LDAP Logins</strong>: Choose if you want to allow users to log in with their LDAP (Lightweight Directory Access Protocol) credentials. You will need to enter details about your LDAP server (host, port, search base, uid attribute, directory user, directory user password, and whether to use STARTTLS) to enable LDAP Logins.'=>'<strong>启用 LDAP 登录</strong>：选择是否允许用户登录使用他们的 LDAP（轻量级目录访问协议）凭据。你将需要输入有关您的 LDAP 服务器的详细信息（主机、端口、搜索库、uid 属性、目录用户、目录用户密码、是否使用STARTTLS） 启用 LDAP 登录。','<strong>Default role for new CAS users</strong>: Specify which role new external users will get by default. Be sure to choose a role with limited permissions!'=>'<strong>新 CAS 用户的默认角色</strong>：指定新角色默认情况下，外部用户将获得。一定要选择一个角色，有限的权限！','If you enable OAuth2 logins:'=>'如果启用 OAuth2 登录：','<strong>Client ID</strong>: You can generate this ID following the instructions for your specific provider.'=>'<strong>客户端 ID：</strong>您可以按照针对特定提供商的说明。','<strong>Client Secret</strong>: You can generate this secret by following the instructions for your specific provider.'=>'""<strong>客户端密码</strong>：您可以通过遵循针对特定提供商的说明。','Note: for increased security, you can leave this field blank and instead define this value either in wp-config.php via <code>define( \'AUTHORIZER_OAUTH2_CLIENT_SECRET\', \'...\' );</code>, or you may fetch it from an external service like AWS Secrets Manager by hooking into the <code>authorizer_oauth2_client_secret</code> filter. This will prevent it from being stored in plaintext in the WordPress database.'=>'注意：为了提高安全性，您可以将此字段留空，而是在wp-config.php中定义此值 <code>define（ \'AUTHORIZER_OAUTH2_CLIENT_SECRET\'， \'...\' ）;</code>，或者你可以通过挂接到<code>authorizer_oauth2_client_secret</code>过滤器。这将防止它从以明文形式存储在 WordPress 数据库中。','<strong>Authorization URL</strong>: For the generic OAuth2 provider, you will need to specify the 3 endpoints required for the oauth2 authentication flow. This is the first: the endpoint first contacted to initiate the authentication.'=>'""<strong>授权 URL：</strong>对于通用 OAuth2 提供程序，您将需要指定 OAuth2 身份验证流所需的 3 个端点。这是第一个：首先联系的端点以启动身份验证。','<strong>Access Token URL</strong>: For the generic OAuth2 provider, you will need to specify the 3 endpoints required for the oauth2 authentication flow. This is the second: the endpoint that is contacted after initiation to retrieve an access token for the user that just authenticated.'=>'""<strong>访问令牌 URL：</strong>对于通用 OAuth2 提供程序，您将需要指定 OAuth2 身份验证流所需的 3 个端点。这是第二个：启动后联系的端点检索刚刚通过身份验证的用户的访问令牌。','<strong>Resource Owner URL</strong>: For the generic OAuth2 provider, you will need to specify the 3 endpoints required for the oauth2 authentication flow. This is the third: the endpoint that is contacted after successfully receiving an authentication token to retrieve details on the user that just authenticated.'=>'<strong>资源所有者 URL：</strong>对于通用 OAuth2 提供程序，您将需要指定 OAuth2 身份验证所需的 3 个端点流动。这是第三个：成功后联系的端点接收身份验证令牌以检索有关用户的详细信息，只是已认证。','If you enable Google logins:'=>'如果您启用 Google 登录：','<strong>Google Client ID</strong>: You can generate this ID by creating a new Project in the <a href=\'https://cloud.google.com/console\'>Google Developers Console</a>. A Client ID typically looks something like this: 1234567890123-kdjr85yt6vjr6d8g7dhr8g7d6durjf7g.apps.googleusercontent.com'=>'<strong>Google 客户端 ID：</strong>您可以通过创建一个新的项目在<a href=\'https：//cloud.google.com/console\'>Google Developers 控制台</a>。客户端 ID 通常如下所示：1234567890123-kdjr85yt6vjr6d8g7dhr8g7d6durjf7g.apps.googleusercontent.com','<strong>Google Client Secret</strong>: You can generate this secret by creating a new Project in the <a href=\'https://cloud.google.com/console\'>Google Developers Console</a>. A Client Secret typically looks something like this: sDNgX5_pr_5bly-frKmvp8jT'=>'<strong>Google 客户端密码</strong>：您可以通过以下方式生成此密码在<a href=\'https：//cloud.google.com/console\'>Google Developers Console</a>.客户端密钥通常显示为像这样的东西：sDNgX5_pr_5bly-frKmvp8jT','Note: for increased security, you can leave this field blank and instead define this value either in wp-config.php via <code>define( \'AUTHORIZER_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET\', \'...\' );</code>, or you may fetch it from an external service like AWS Secrets Manager by hooking into the <code>authorizer_google_client_secret</code> filter. This will prevent it from being stored in plaintext in the WordPress database.'=>'注意：为了提高安全性，您可以将此字段留空，而是在wp-config.php中定义此值 <code>define（ \'AUTHORIZER_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET\'， \'...\' ）;</code>，或者你可以通过挂接到<code>authorizer_google_client_secret</code>过滤器。这将防止它从以明文形式存储在 WordPress 数据库中。','If you enable CAS logins:'=>'如果启用 CAS 登录：','<strong>CAS server hostname</strong>: Enter the hostname of the CAS server you authenticate against (e.g., authn.example.edu).'=>'<strong>CAS 服务器主机名</strong>：输入 CAS 服务器的主机名您针对（例如，authn.example.edu）进行身份验证。','<strong>CAS server port</strong>: Enter the port on the CAS server to connect to (e.g., 443).'=>'<strong>CAS 服务器端口</strong>：输入 CAS 服务器上的端口进行连接到（例如，443）。','<strong>CAS server path/context</strong>: Enter the path to the login endpoint on the CAS server (e.g., /cas).'=>'<strong>CAS 服务器路径/上下文</strong>：输入登录路径CAS 服务器上的端点（例如 /cas）。','<strong>CAS server method</strong>: Select the method to use when setting the CAS config (e.g.,"client" or "proxy")'=>'<strong>CAS 服务器方法</strong>：选择设置CAS 配置（例如，客户端或代理）','<strong>CAS attribute containing first name</strong>: Enter the CAS attribute that has the user\'s first name. When this user first logs in, their WordPress account will have their first name retrieved from CAS and added to their WordPress profile.'=>'<strong>包含名字的 CAS 属性</strong>：输入 CAS 属性这有用户的名字。当这个用户第一次登录时，他们的WordPress帐户将从 CAS 检索他们的名字并添加到他们的WordPress个人资料。','<strong>CAS attribute containing last name</strong>: Enter the CAS attribute that has the user\'s last name. When this user first logs in, their WordPress account will have their last name retrieved from CAS and added to their WordPress profile.'=>'<strong>包含姓氏的 CAS 属性</strong>：输入 CAS 属性那有用户的姓氏。当这个用户第一次登录时，他们的WordPress帐户将从 CAS 检索他们的姓氏并添加到他们的WordPress个人资料。','<strong>CAS attribute update</strong>: Select whether the first and last names retrieved from CAS should overwrite any value the user has entered in the first and last name fields in their WordPress profile. If this is not set, this only happens the first time they log in.'=>'<strong>CAS 属性更新</strong>：选择第一个和最后一个 从 CAS 检索到的名称应覆盖用户在他们的 WordPress 个人资料中的名字和姓氏字段。如果这不是设置，这只发生在他们第一次登录时。','If you enable LDAP logins:'=>'如果启用 LDAP 登录：','<strong>LDAP Host</strong>: Enter the URL of the LDAP server you authenticate against.'=>'<strong>LDAP 主机</strong>：输入您验证的 LDAP 服务器的 URL反对。','<strong>LDAP Port</strong>: Enter the port number that the LDAP server listens on.'=>'<strong>LDAP端口</strong>：输入LDAP服务器的端口号听着。','<strong>LDAP Search Base</strong>: Enter the LDAP string that represents the search base, e.g., ou=people,dc=example,dc=edu'=>'<strong>LDAP 搜索库</strong>：输入表示搜索库的 LDAP 字符串，例如 ou=people，dc=example，dc=edu','<strong>LDAP Search Filter</strong>: Enter the optional LDAP string that represents the search filter, e.g., (memberOf=cn=wp_users,ou=people,dc=example,dc=edu)'=>'<strong>LDAP 搜索过滤器</strong>：输入表示搜索过滤器的可选 LDAP 字符串，例如 （memberOf=cn=wp_users，ou=people，dc=example，dc=edu）','<strong>LDAP attribute containing username</strong>: Enter the name of the LDAP attribute that contains the usernames used by those attempting to log in. The plugin will search on this attribute to find the cn to bind against for login attempts.'=>'<strong>包含用户名的 LDAP 属性</strong>：输入包含尝试登录的用户使用的用户名的 LDAP 属性的名称。插件将搜索此属性以查找要绑定登录尝试的 cn。','<strong>LDAP Directory User</strong>: Enter the name of the LDAP user that has permissions to browse the directory.'=>'<strong>LDAP 目录用户</strong>：输入有权浏览目录的 LDAP 用户的名称。','Note: for increased security, you can leave this field blank and instead define this value either in wp-config.php via <code>define( \'AUTHORIZER_LDAP_USER\', \'...\' );</code>, or you may fetch it from an external service like AWS Secrets Manager by hooking into the <code>authorizer_ldap_user</code> filter. This will prevent it from being stored in plaintext in the WordPress database.'=>'注意：为了提高安全性，您可以将此字段留空，而是通过 <code>define（ \'AUTHORIZER_LDAP_USER\'， \'...\' ）;</code> 在wp-config.php中定义此值，也可以通过挂接到 <code>authorizer_ldap_user</code> 筛选条件从 AWS Secrets Manager 等外部服务获取此值。这将防止它以明文形式存储在 WordPress 数据库中。','<strong>LDAP Directory User Password</strong>: Enter the password for the LDAP user that has permission to browse the directory.'=>'<strong>LDAP 目录用户密码</strong>：输入有权浏览目录的 LDAP 用户的密码。','Note: for increased security, you can leave this field blank and instead define this value either in wp-config.php via <code>define( \'AUTHORIZER_LDAP_PASSWORD\', \'...\' );</code>, or you may fetch it from an external service like AWS Secrets Manager by hooking into the <code>authorizer_ldap_password</code> filter. This will prevent it from being stored in the WordPress database.'=>'注意：为了提高安全性，您可以将此字段留空，而是通过 <code>define（ \'AUTHORIZER_LDAP_PASSWORD\'， \'...\' ）;</code> 在wp-config.php中定义此值，也可以通过挂接到 <code>authorizer_ldap_password</code> 筛选条件从 AWS Secrets Manager 等外部服务获取该值。这将防止它存储在 WordPress 数据库中。','<strong>Use STARTTLS</strong>: Select whether unencrypted communication with the LDAP server should be upgraded to a TLS-secured connection using STARTTLS.'=>'<strong>使用 STARTTLS</strong>：选择是否应使用 STARTTLS 将与 LDAP 服务器的未加密通信升级为受 TLS 保护的连接。','<strong>Custom lost password URL</strong>: The WordPress login page contains a link to recover a lost password. If you have external users who shouldn\'t change the password on their WordPress account, point them to the appropriate location to change the password on their external authentication service here.'=>'<strong>自定义丢失密码 URL：</strong>WordPress 登录页面包含用于恢复丢失密码的链接。如果您有外部用户不应更改其 WordPress 帐户上的密码，请在此处将他们指向适当的位置以更改其外部身份验证服务的密码。','<strong>LDAP attribute containing first name</strong>: Enter the LDAP attribute that has the user\'s first name. When this user first logs in, their WordPress account will have their first name retrieved from LDAP and added to their WordPress profile.'=>'<strong>包含名字的 LDAP 属性</strong>：输入具有用户名字的 LDAP 属性。当此用户首次登录时，他们的 WordPress 帐户将从 LDAP 检索他们的名字并添加到他们的 WordPress 个人资料中。','<strong>LDAP attribute containing last name</strong>: Enter the LDAP attribute that has the user\'s last name. When this user first logs in, their WordPress account will have their last name retrieved from LDAP and added to their WordPress profile.'=>'<strong>包含姓氏的 LDAP 属性</strong>：输入包含用户姓氏的 LDAP 属性。当该用户首次登录时，他们的 WordPress 帐户将从 LDAP 检索他们的姓氏并添加到他们的 WordPress 个人资料中。','<strong>LDAP attribute update</strong>: Select whether the first and last names retrieved from LDAP should overwrite any value the user has entered in the first and last name fields in their WordPress profile. If this is not set, this only happens the first time they log in.'=>'<strong>LDAP 属性更新</strong>：选择从 LDAP 检索到的名字和姓氏是否应覆盖用户在其 WordPress 配置文件中的名字和姓氏字段中输入的任何值。如果未设置此设置，则仅在他们第一次登录时发生。','External Service'=>'外部服务','<strong>Limit invalid login attempts</strong>: Choose how soon (and for how long) to restrict access to individuals (or bots) making repeated invalid login attempts. You may set a shorter delay first, and then a longer delay after repeated invalid attempts; you may also set how much time must pass before the delays will be reset to normal.'=>'<strong>限制无效登录尝试</strong>：选择限制重复无效登录尝试的个人（或机器人）访问的时间（以及持续时间）。您可以先设置较短的延迟，然后在重复无效尝试后设置较长的延迟;您还可以设置延迟重置为正常之前必须经过多少时间。','<strong>Hide WordPress Logins</strong>: If you want to hide the WordPress username and password fields and the Log In button on the wp-login screen, enable this option. Note: You can always access the WordPress logins by adding external=wordpress to the wp-login URL, like so:'=>'<strong>隐藏 WordPress 登录</strong>：如果要隐藏 WordPress 用户名和密码字段以及 wp-login 屏幕上的“登录”按钮，请启用此选项。注意：您始终可以通过将 external=wordpress 添加到 wp-login URL 来访问 WordPress 登录名，如下所示：','<strong>Disable WordPress Logins</strong>: If you want to prevent users from logging in with their WordPress passwords and instead only allow logins from external services, enable this option. Note: enabling this will also hide WordPress logins unless the LDAP external service is enabled.'=>'<strong>禁用 WordPress 登录</strong>：如果要阻止用户使用其 WordPress 密码登录，而只允许从外部服务登录，请启用此选项。注意：启用此功能也会隐藏 WordPress 登录，除非启用了 LDAP 外部服务。','<strong>Custom WordPress login branding</strong>: If you\'d like to use custom branding on the WordPress login page, select that here. You will need to use the `authorizer_add_branding_option` filter in your theme to add it. You can see an example theme that implements this filter in the plugin directory under sample-theme-add-branding.'=>'<strong>自定义 WordPress 登录品牌</strong>：如果您想在 WordPress 登录页面上使用自定义品牌，请在此处选择。您需要使用主题中的“authorizer_add_branding_option”过滤器来添加它。您可以在 sample-theme-add-branding 下的插件目录中看到实现此过滤器的示例主题。','Advanced'=>'高级','Can\'t reach CAS server. Please provide'=>'无法访问 CAS 服务器。请提供','accurate CAS settings'=>'准确的 CAS 设置','if you intend to use it.'=>'如果您打算使用它。','Settings'=>'设置','Network Settings'=>'网络设置','Who can log into the site?'=>'谁可以登录网站？','Which role should receive email notifications about pending users?'=>'哪个角色应接收有关待处理用户的电子邮件通知？','What message should pending users see after attempting to log in?'=>'待处理用户在尝试登录后应看到什么消息？','What message should blocked users see after attempting to log in?'=>'被阻止的用户在尝试登录后应该看到什么消息？','Send welcome email to new approved users?'=>'是否发送新的邮件给新申请的用户?','Welcome email subject'=>'欢迎邮件主题','Welcome email body'=>'欢迎邮件内容','Who can view the site?'=>'谁可以查看这个网站?','What pages (if any) should be available to everyone?'=>'哪些页面（如果有）应该可供所有人使用？','What happens to people without access when they visit a private page?'=>'没有访问权限的用户在访问私人页面时会发生什么情况？','What happens to people without access when they visit a public page?'=>'没有访问权限的用户在访问公共页面时会发生什么情况？','What message should people without access see?'=>'没有访问权限的人应该看到什么消息？','Default role for new users'=>'新用户的默认角色','OAuth2 Logins'=>'OAuth2登录','Provider'=>'提供商','Custom label'=>'定制标签','Client ID'=>'Client ID','Client Secret'=>'Client Secret','OAuth2 Hosted Domain'=>'OAuth2 安全域名','Tenant ID'=>'Tenant ID','Authorization URL'=>'授权的URL地址','Access Token URL'=>'获取AccessToken的URL地址','Resource Owner URL'=>'获取用户信息的URL地址','Google Logins'=>'Google登录','Google Client ID'=>'Google 客户端 ID','Google Client Secret'=>'Google 客户端密码','Google Hosted Domain'=>'Google 托管域名','CAS Logins'=>'CAS 登录','CAS custom label'=>'CAS 自定义标签','CAS server hostname'=>'CAS 服务器主机名','CAS server port'=>'CAS 服务器端口','CAS server path/context'=>'CAS 服务器路径/上下文','CAS server method'=>'CAS 服务器方法','CAS server protocol'=>'CAS 服务器协议','CAS attribute containing email address'=>'包含电子邮件地址的 CAS 属性','CAS attribute containing first name'=>'包含名字的 CAS 属性','CAS attribute containing last name'=>'包含姓氏的 CAS 属性','CAS attribute update'=>'CAS 属性更新','CAS automatic login'=>'CAS 自动登录','CAS users linked by username'=>'按用户名链接的 CAS 用户','LDAP Logins'=>'LDAP 登录','LDAP Host'=>'LDAP 主机','LDAP Port'=>'LDAP 端口','Use STARTTLS'=>'使用 STARTTLS','LDAP Search Base'=>'LDAP 搜索库','LDAP Search Filter'=>'LDAP 搜索过滤器','LDAP attribute containing username'=>'包含用户名的 LDAP 属性','LDAP attribute containing email address'=>'包含电子邮件地址的 LDAP 属性','LDAP Directory User'=>'LDAP 目录用户','LDAP Directory User Password'=>'LDAP 目录用户密码','Custom lost password URL'=>'自定义丢失密码 URL','LDAP attribute containing first name'=>'包含名字的 LDAP 属性','LDAP attribute containing last name'=>'包含姓氏的 LDAP 属性','LDAP attribute update'=>'LDAP 属性更新','LDAP test connection'=>'LDAP 测试连接','Limit invalid login attempts'=>'限制无效登录尝试','Hide WordPress Login'=>'隐藏 WordPress 登录','Disable WordPress Logins'=>'禁用 WordPress 登录','Custom WordPress login branding'=>'自定义 WordPress 登录品牌','Authorizer admin menu item location'=>'授权方管理菜单项位置','Show custom usermeta in user list'=>'在用户列表中显示自定义 usermeta','Number of users per page'=>'每页用户数','Approved users sort method'=>'已批准的用户排序方法','Approved users sort order'=>'已批准的用户排序顺序','Show dashboard widget to admin users'=>'向管理员用户显示仪表板小组件','Override multisite options'=>'覆盖多站点选项','Authorizer Settings'=>'授权方设置','You do not have sufficient permissions to access this page.'=>'您没有足够的权限来访问此页面。','Most <strong>Authorizer</strong> settings are set in the individual sites, but you can specify a few options here that apply to <strong>all sites in the network</strong>. These settings will override settings in the individual sites.'=>'大多